33
34class VideoBitrateAllocator;
35class VideoBitrateAllocationObserver;
36
37namespace vcm {
38
39class VCMProcessTimer {
40 public:
41 static const int64_t kDefaultProcessIntervalMs = 1000;
42
43 VCMProcessTimer(int64_t periodMs, Clock* clock)
44 : _clock(clock),
45 _periodMs(periodMs),
46 _latestMs(_clock->TimeInMilliseconds()) {}
47 int64_t Period() const;
48 int64_t TimeUntilProcess() const;
49 void Processed();
50
51 private:
52 Clock* _clock;
53 int64_t _periodMs;
54 int64_t _latestMs;
55};
56
57class VideoReceiver : public Module {
58 public:
59 VideoReceiver(Clock* clock, VCMTiming* timing);
60 ~VideoReceiver() override;
61
62 int32_t RegisterReceiveCodec(uint8_t payload_type,
63 const VideoCodec* receiveCodec,
64 int32_t numberOfCores);
65
66 void RegisterExternalDecoder(VideoDecoder* externalDecoder,
67 uint8_t payloadType);
68 int32_t RegisterReceiveCallback(VCMReceiveCallback* receiveCallback);
69 int32_t RegisterFrameTypeCallback(VCMFrameTypeCallback* frameTypeCallback);
70 int32_t RegisterPacketRequestCallback(VCMPacketRequestCallback* callback);
71
72 int32_t Decode(uint16_t maxWaitTimeMs);
73
74 int32_t IncomingPacket(const uint8_t* incomingPayload,
75 size_t payloadLength,
76 const RTPHeader& rtp_header,
77 const RTPVideoHeader& video_header);
78
79 void SetNackSettings(size_t max_nack_list_size,
80 int max_packet_age_to_nack,
81 int max_incomplete_time_ms);
82
83 int64_t TimeUntilNextProcess() override;
84 void Process() override;
85 void ProcessThreadAttached(ProcessThread* process_thread) override;
86
87 protected:
88 int32_t Decode(const webrtc::VCMEncodedFrame& frame);
89 int32_t RequestKeyFrame();
90
91 private:
92 // Used for DCHECKing thread correctness.
93 // In build where DCHECKs are enabled, will return false before
94 // DecoderThreadStarting is called, then true until DecoderThreadStopped
95 // is called.
96 // In builds where DCHECKs aren't enabled, it will return true.
97 bool IsDecoderThreadRunning();
98
99 SequenceChecker construction_thread_checker_;
100 SequenceChecker decoder_thread_checker_;
101 SequenceChecker module_thread_checker_;
102 Clock* const clock_;
103 Mutex process_mutex_;
104 VCMTiming* _timing;
105 VCMReceiver _receiver;
106 VCMDecodedFrameCallback _decodedFrameCallback;
107
108 // These callbacks are set on the construction thread before being attached
109 // to the module thread or decoding started, so a lock is not required.
110 VCMFrameTypeCallback* _frameTypeCallback;
111 VCMPacketRequestCallback* _packetRequestCallback;
112
113 // Used on both the module and decoder thread.
114 bool _scheduleKeyRequest RTC_GUARDED_BY(process_mutex_);
115 bool drop_frames_until_keyframe_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(process_mutex_);
116
117 // Modified on the construction thread while not attached to the process
118 // thread. Once attached to the process thread, its value is only read
119 // so a lock is not required.
120 size_t max_nack_list_size_;
121
122 // Callbacks are set before the decoder thread starts.
123 // Once the decoder thread has been started, usage of |_codecDataBase| moves
124 // over to the decoder thread.
125 VCMDecoderDataBase _codecDataBase;
126
127 VCMProcessTimer _retransmissionTimer RTC_GUARDED_BY(module_thread_checker_);
128 VCMProcessTimer _keyRequestTimer RTC_GUARDED_BY(module_thread_checker_);
129 ThreadUnsafeOneTimeEvent first_frame_received_
130 RTC_GUARDED_BY(decoder_thread_checker_);
131 // Modified on the construction thread. Can be read without a lock and assumed
132 // to be non-null on the module and decoder threads.
133 ProcessThread* process_thread_ = nullptr;
134 bool is_attached_to_process_thread_
135 RTC_GUARDED_BY(construction_thread_checker_) = false;
136};
137
138} // namespace vcm
139} // namespace webrtc
140#endif // MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_VIDEO_CODING_IMPL_H_
